Melissa Klein and her husband Aaron refused to make a wedding cake for Rachel Bowman-Cryer and her wife Laurel in 2013 because they disapprove of gay marriage . 
  They were found guilty of discrimination earlier this year and must pay $135,000 to the couple . 
  The couple said they suffered emotional distress and received death threats because of the case . 
  Sweet Cakes by Melissa in Portland closed in 2013 after the couple filed a civil rights lawsuit . 
  The Kleins say they are in dire financial straits and have raised $100,000 from anonymous donors on GoFundMe . 
 